@kflay new album art MONO! K.Flay was one of the first artist I ever got to work with over a decade ago, she took a chance on me and brought me on tour. She’s one of the smartest, hard working, and witty people I’ve ever met and I’m lucky to call her a friend. When she asked me to do her cover for the new album, I was flattered and grateful for the opportunity. Thanks to the whole team who brought this to life, we didn’t photoshop her and did this practically.

Super excited to share key art imagery I shot for @geffenplayhouse new show The Mountaintop. This was one of those dream projects where the casting, set design, and costume design were all so beautiful and aligned. I was lucky enough to have the time to light the whole shoot how I wanted and tinker with everything to get exactly what was in my head captured in camera. We ended up using 9 light sources. And yes, we had a rain machine dumping water outside the window to capture that practically too 🤓

Super grateful that I’ve had the opportunity to work with such a wonderful client on an ongoing basis for the past few years and hope to continue the collaboration for years to come. 

Swipe for BTS

AI is both scary and exciting and how I feel about it changes every day. Some days I’m terrified it’s going to take away my livelihood as a photographer and other days I see it as an amazing tool to help bring my abstract vision to life. Here’s a shoot I did where I photographed the talent practically and built my dream topiary garden in AI (much like using a background plate of a photograph) and composited them together. Doing this process made me realize I much l prefer shooting the process of shooting practically when I can but sometimes it’s not possible.
